<HEADER>
A1460 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s BC-SUPERBOWL-TV-TEX     01-31 1278
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SUPER </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MORE THAN EIGHT HOURS OF COVERAGE HAD ITS MOMENTS BUT NOT ENOUGH
</HEADLINE>
 BOWL-TV-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICHIE WHITT 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Stupor start, Super finish and 81/2 hours of couch potato utopia
between.
</P>
<P>
   With neither the Rams nor Titans possessing any history,
villains or captivating story lines going into Super Bowl XXXIV,
there was little interest going in. Despite the Rams' 23-16 poorly
played escape ending up closer than a Roy Firestone interview,
there is even less coming out.
</P>
<P>
   If not for Toni Braxton's ridiculously bad lip-synching, David
Blaine's mesmerizing magic or creative commercials featuring God
splattering Tabasco, cowboys herding cats and ``Whazzuupp?!''
exchanges, the 130 million of us American viewers would've flipped
over prematurely to TBS's ``Matlock'' marathon instead of enduring
ABC's four-hour pregame and an elaborately silly halftime show
weaved around an absolutely mundane football game almost bailed out
by a climactic conclusion.
</P>
<P>
   While the Rams fill the Georgia Dome's postgame podium with
Jesus and tears before getting fitted for their tainted crowns as
the best team of the NFL's worst season, a look back at 34 reasons
Super Bowl XXXIV felt more like a random game and less like a
monumental event:
</P>
<P>
   1. The Titans came within one yard of pulling off the greatest
comeback in Super Bowl history. Inexplicably, ABC analyst Boomer
Esiason capped his awful performance by calling Tennessee's
game-losing pass a ``terrific play call.'' Seems like a better idea
would've been to throw it into the end zone.
</P>
<P>
   2. ABC obviously needed another week to prepare. It twice came
back early from commercials (once catching Al Michaels singing),
three times missed penalty flags and once missed an entire play.
</P>
<P>
   3. ``The View's'' Meredith Vieira actually said the Super Bowl
``is all about the butts'' and the Question of the Day was ``Would
women watch the game if players wore looser pants?'' Imagine the
National Organization of Women's reaction if NBC's Jim Gray
previewed a WNBA playoff game by saying, ``It's all about the
cleavage.''
</P>
<P>
   4. The bad news: ABC's pregame show lasted four hours. The good
news: Fox's show last year lasted seven hours.
</P>
<P>
   5. Sideline reporter Leslie Visser, who sported a mushroom
hairstyle and a suit right out of Sigfried &AMP; Roy's Vegas closet,
actually quoted Mike Tyson coming out of halftime.
</P>
<P>
   6. Don't be ashamed if you were caught in a dot.com daze all
day. The pregame show was sponsored by, in order, OurBeginning.com,
Britannica.com, Hewlitt Packard, WebMD.com, MicroStrategy.com and
Motorola. That, of course, was followed by the Charles Schwab
kickoff show, the E-Trade halftime show and capped off by the
Lincoln Post-Game show.
</P>
<P>
   7. Rams owner Georgia Frontiere: 7 husbands, 1 championship.
</P>
<P>
   8. Lie of the day belonged to Hershey executive Mike Pasquale,
who told a kicker attempting to win $1 million, ``We were rooting
for you.'' Instead, the kicker missed and Pasquale handed him a
check for only $10,000.
</P>
<P>
   9. During chef Emeril Lagasse's pregame cooking feature, fans
actually cheered garlic.
</P>
<P>
   10. Second-most competitive score of the day: Shots of Brenda
Warner and her feathered sweater 10, Mechelle McNair 7.
</P>
<P>
   11. He wasn't alone, but ABC stand-in analyst Steve Young looked
silly by predicting early in the day that ``the Rams will hang 40
points on this Titans defense.''
</P>
<P>
   12. Can the day be far off when the Microsoft.com Seahawks host
the Visa Cowboys?
</P>
<P>
   13. Who really wants to be a millionaire? Just prove you
predicted Kurt Warner to be Super Bowl MVP back in July.
</P>
<P>
   14. How long will it be before the NAACP calls to pull
Budweiser's ``Whazzuupp?!'' ads because they degrade the
communication skills of African-Americans? Hopefully, they'll wait
until we get a few more chuckles out of them.
</P>
<P>
   15. Of all the talent at ABC's disposal, it had ``Good Morning
America's'' Charles Gibson conduct its one-on-one with Titans coach
Jeff Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   16. Vince Lombardi likely rolled in his grave despite the
late-game suspense. With the game on the line, the Rams repeatedly
lined up offsides, Titans running back Eddie George blocked a
cornerback while a pass hit him in the elbow and Tennessee
inexplicably called a game-deciding play that didn't go into the
end zone.
</P>
<P>
   17. You think the dot.com business is confusing; former
Wimbledon champ Boris Becker was introduced as ``NFL Ambassador to
Europe.''
</P>
<P>
   18. Were we groggy, or does Rams offensive coordinator Mike
Martz bear a resemblance to new Cowboys coach Dave Campo?
</P>
<P>
   19. Explain to us again the theory of wearing eye black in a
dome. Under that premise, shouldn't all NBA players get painted?
</P>
<P>
   20. There was finally a Barry Sanders sighting Sunday, albeit a
cameo in a Charles Schwab commercial.
</P>
<P>
   21. Despite ABC's countless talking heads, it was Gus the Volvo
truck driver who provided the best insight: ``Your haircut
shouldn't cost more than your hat.'' Amen.
</P>
<P>
   22. The Titans made a good showing, but they did it in the
worst-looking uniforms to ever disgrace a Super Bowl. Can you say
``Roller Derby rejects?''
</P>
<P>
   23. If the game had any early electricity, it was unplugged when
Titans safety Blaine Bishop was knocked out of the game and carted
off midway through the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
   24. With decent, hard-working players and coaches on both
sidelines, it was almost impossible to love or hate either team.
Unless, of course, you live in Nashville, Tenn., St. Louis or had a
vested financial interest in everything from the coin flip to the
final score.
</P>
<P>
   25. Play of the day? Magician Blaine tore up the 7 of Clubs and
put it in the hand of Titans tight end Jackie Harris. He then, just
seconds later, squeezed Harris' hand and told him to open his
fingers, revealing the 7 of Hearts, un-torn.
</P>
<P>
   26. We longed for more of a snappy pregame intro that featured
``Seinfeld's'' Kramer, Wynonna and Tiger Woods, and cringed each
time former Saints coach Mike Ditka shamelessly plugged the movie,
``Runaway Bride,'' on video.
</P>
<P>
   27. Commentator Jim ``Grandpa'' McKay was kind enough to let us
sit at his knee while he spun old-school yarns about how we should
have sympathy for NFL players because ``they take enormous physical
abuse.'' He left out the part about how they make more in a month
than most of us in a year, and how they don't have to go back to
work until July.
</P>
<P>
   28. Only thing more glaringly absent Sunday than Rams running
back Marshall Faulk? Nike.
</P>
<P>
   29. Halftime performer Phil Collins' pregame stint consisted of
coughing into his hand, using the same hand to shake with Chris
Berman, admitting he doesn't ``understand the NFL game'' and then
saying he would root for the Titans because ``they're from
Tennessee, and I used to be a Davey Crockett fan.''
</P>
<P>
   30. What was so Super about offenses driving down the field,
stalling at the 30 and settling for missed field goals? Cowboys
fans saw that all season.
</P>
<P>
   31. Rams holder Mike Horan became the oldest player to ever drop
a perfect snap from center in a Super Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   32. Just didn't look right for a Super Bowl coach (Jeff Fisher)
to be wearing an Old Navy fleece vest on the sideline. Tom Landry
and his fedora never looked better.
</P>
<P>
   33. In case you _ like him _ missed it, that was Anthony Dorsett
missing a tackle on Isaac Bruce's game-winning touchdown catch.
</P>
<P>
   34. In retrospect, ABC should've just run three hours of the
greatest runs by No. 34, Walter Payton.
</P>
<P>
   40. Winks straight ahead. If you made it through the whole 8 1/2
hours, you more than earned it.
</P>
<P>
   165. Days until training camps open. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-31-00 0151EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
