<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Oh, stick it in your ear!
 &HT;    By Gregory Kallenberg
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Hey! There's a guy walking down the street
talking to himself! No, wait a second, he has an earpiece and it's
attached to a cell phone. You thought cell phones were annoying
enough as it is, but this new attachment for the phone takes the
cell to newly annoying heights. People claim the new attachment is
designed to avoid radiation, but we know this is yet another
advancement in cell phone vanity. In particular, the Jabra headset
attachment ranks as the most annoying. The headphone fits snugly
into the ear and a wire, holding an inconspicuous plastic
microphone, runs down to the cell phone. Now people who wanted to
look cool talking on their cell phones can look cooler by looking
like they're talking to no one at all.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
