 &HT;    Keeping an eye out for the groundhog's shadow
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The famous groundhog Punxsutawney Phil will search for
his shadow Wednesday. If no shadow appears, then the superstitious
believe spring is here. If he sees his shadow, it signals another
six weeks of winter. Crowds of 30,000 have visited Punxsutawney,
Pa., to get a glimpse of the groundhog. Join the ``hog''-tivities
at the official site of the Punxsutawney Groundhog Club at
www.groundhog.org.
</P>
