 &HT;    One hip rhythm clip
 &HT;    By Gregory Kallenberg
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ If you can't wait for Sony's Memorystick Walkman
to come out, might I suggest picking up its Music Clip ($300,
www.sony.com) to sate that hankering to rock out on Internet tunes.
The clip comes in silver or black and is about the size of a really
fat pen. The Clip ports directly with Sony's VAIO USB connectors
(or any other PC USB connectors) and comes with the ability to
decode MP3s and ATRAC3s. The device also comes complete with a
built-in 64MB flash memory card _ which will allow up to 120
minutes of music files _ and an onboard equalizing system with
``rock,'' ``pop'' and ``jazz'' presets. Once everything is
downloaded, just plug in your favorite set of headphones and you
have an instant party in your head. The Music Clip is bundled with
OpenMG Jukebox, so you can manage your music files. This program
allows you to download and organize music files as well as record
and store your favorite tunes from your favorite CDs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gregory Kallenberg
</P>
