<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-31 10:53 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1673 &Cx1f; tad-z
r k BC-COMMENTARY-BJT01-COX     01-31 0615
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT01-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Tuesday, February 1, 2000 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   EDIT-ABERNATHY _ Tis a pity that Ralph David Abernathy III
squandered his heritage and must serve four years in prison. But
the damage to career and good family name is self-inflicted.
(Atlanta Constitution). 7.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ Recently, I wrote of the plight of my friend
Gail, a dedicated lady who found the schoolhouse locked when she
tried to realize her dream of teaching high school history. After
completing her education (cum laude and post-kids), she has been
unable to land a job in anybody's school system because she has two
strikes against her: a master's degree, and her age. Feedback from
readers. (Schuett, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: The following is designed to run as the first of two
consecutive columns on the same subject or be merged into one op-ed
or perspective section piece by merely deleting the dateline and
lede of the second section. Either piece also could stand alone.
Both are available on the Cox and New York Times wires. Since this
is the hiring season for next fall's crop of teachers, a local
situationer is suggested. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   HERRIN-COLUMN _ The latest storm of the century. (Herrin, Rocky
Mount Telegram). 16.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA, Fla. _ There's anything wrong with New
Hampshire and Iowa. This time of year, I'm sure they are great
places to be from. But they don't deserve their prominence in
presidential campaigns. No state does. There is no state where
people are so wise and representative of the rest of us that they
should have the power to choose the president for everyone else.
The fact that no state would ever knowingly reproduce the
presidential primary system for choosing state officials should be
a clue this is a system that makes no sense. (Lane, Daytona Beach
News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
<P>
   Spot news budgets move daily at 2 p.m. and 6 p.m. Eastern.
Additionally, separate features and commentary budgets move at 10
a.m., and sports and business budgets at 6 p.m. Additional updates
are possible if news developments warrant.
</P>
<P>
   All times are Eastern unless otherwise noted. If stories will
move after 8 p.m., an ETA will be given.
</P>
