<P>
   EDIT-ABERNATHY _ Tis a pity that Ralph David Abernathy III
squandered his heritage and must serve four years in prison. But
the damage to career and good family name is self-inflicted.
(Atlanta Constitution). 7.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ Recently, I wrote of the plight of my friend
Gail, a dedicated lady who found the schoolhouse locked when she
tried to realize her dream of teaching high school history. After
completing her education (cum laude and post-kids), she has been
unable to land a job in anybody's school system because she has two
strikes against her: a master's degree, and her age. Feedback from
readers. (Schuett, Cox News Service)
</P>
