   OXYGEN _ Every major media company, from Time Warner to Disney,
has tried to corral woman viewers as their own. None have yet
succeeded. Can Oxygen, a new woman's channel pioneered by Nike
legend Gerry Laybourne, succeed where the giants have stumbled? We
explain her strategy and examine, through the lens of industry
observers, its chances of success. (Kloer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 35.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   OXGERRY: A profile of Gerry Laybourne, Oxygen's CEO. It's a look
at what she did at Nickelodeon and how that history might shape
Oxygen. (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTNEY _ It's 1976 _ six years after The Beatles' painful
breakup. Paul McCartney is riding around New York City in a stretch
limo. Suddenly he gets a loopy urge to pay John Lennon an
unexpected visit at his spacious Manhattan apartment. (Thompson,
Palm Beach Post). 30. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NEWSSTAND _ Periodicals on the newsstands this week. (O'Briant,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
