<HEADLINE>
`BOWFINGER' SILLY SLAPSTICK; `DON'T LOOK BACK' IS TOPS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Bowfinger'' (DVD) _ Last year, this Eddie
Murphy-Steve Martin Hollywood parody was released around the same
time as Albert Brooks's ``The Muse.'' ``Bowfinger'' is a silly
slapstick patchwork with some moderately amusing moments, but it
did great at the box office, while Brooks's more sophisticated take
on the movie business faltered. No accounting for taste.
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't Look Back'' (DVD) _ D. A. Pennebaker made documentaries
on musicians before the genre was transformed into marketing fluff
by MTV and others. In 1965, Pennebaker followed the squirrelly Bob
Dylan on his tour of England. If you've only seen a scratchy 16mm
version, check out the remastered DVD. The sound is first rate, and
the disc includes a few extra songs and a great version of ``It's
All Over Now, Baby Blue.''
</P>
<P>
   ``In Search of Kundun With Martin Scorsese'' _ The title doesn't
exactly scream for attention, but this is a well-done documentary
and should fascinate anyone who's interested in Scorsese's work,
his fascination with Tibet, or the Dalai Lama. The latter gets
considerable screen time and is as quietly persuasive as you might
imagine _ but for movie fans, the behind-the-scenes footage of
Scorsese at work may be the reason to rent the tape.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Feb. 1: ``Love Stinks'' (DVD), ``The Winslow
Boy'' (DVD), ``The Cabinet of Dr. Caligari,'' ``Nosferatu.'' Feb.
8: ``Blue Streak'' (DVD), ``Fist of the Legend,'' ``Romance,''
``Absence of the Good'' (DVD), ``Ruby Bridges.'' Feb. 15: ``Grey
Wolf,'' ``Breakfast of Champions,'' ``Mob Queen,'' ``Big Fella''
(DVD), ``Song of Freedom'' (DVD), ``In Too Deep,'' ``Daughters of
the Dust'' (DVD), ``Total Recall 2070,'' ``Entropy,'' ``Joe the
King'' (DVD), ``The Lovers on the Bridge.'' Feb. 22: ``Get
Bruce!,'' ``Bats,'' ``Tail Lights Fade'' (DVD), ``Galaxina,''
``Conspirators of Pleasure'' (DVD). Feb. 29: ``Stigmata'' (DVD),
``Random Hearts'' (DVD), ``The Suburbans'' (DVD), ``One Man's
Hero'' (DVD).
</P>
</TEXT>
