<P>
   NH-INSURGENTS (Concord, N.H.) _ The insurgents battling front
runners in their respective parties _ Republican Sen. John McCain
and Democrat Bill Bradley _ face dramatically different challenges
in the days ahead as they wrap up their campaigns in New
Hampshire's first-in-the-nation primary. McCain is hoping a strong
New Hampshire showing will enable him to make inroads against Texas
Gov. George Bush in battleground states that lie ahead. Bradley,
bracing for a second setback at the hands of Vice President Al
Gore, looks to later primaries to rescue his faltering campaign. By
STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (`k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Once again, Sen. John McCain got it
right. He is the only anti-abortion Republican presidential
candidate with the wisdom and courage to acknowledge that a
pregnant woman may have powerful, legitimate reasons not to bear
her child. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
