   BOOK-MISSING (Undated) _ Like the finest fear-practitioners,
Margot Livesey knows that the creepiest moments of life generally
insert themselves into an ordinary day. By Gail Caldwell. 1130
words.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-SHOSTAKOVICH (Undated) _ Dmitriy Shostakovich was a quiet
and private man, but his musical genius made him an international
celebrity in a troubled time. By Richard Dyer. 1550 words.
