   INDONESIA-RIGHTS (Jakarta) _ Indonesian human rights
investigators on Monday accused former military commander Gen.
Wiranto and other top generals of being responsible for ``crimes
against humanity'' in East Timor. President Wahid says he'll ask
Wiranto to resign. By Seth Mydans.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-TERROR (Tokyo) _ A Japanese security commission ruled
Monday that the sect that killed 12 people in a nerve gas attack on
the Tokyo subway in 1995 continues to pose a threat to society and
instructed security authorities to put the sect under surveillance
for up to three years. By Calvin Sims.
