</P>
<P>
   &UR; BUMPER STICKER OF THE WEEK &LR;  &QC; :
</P>
<P>
   ``If we stop voting, will they all go away?'' (Observed on Route
35 between Ames and Waterloo, Iowa) &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DANGEROUS DRINK OF THE WEEK &LR;  &QC; :
</P>
<P>
   Cream soda, blamed by Bill Bradley for his recent bouts of
irregular heartbeats. Bradley's usual drink is Gatorade, which,
unlike cream soda, contains no caffeine to pump you up. &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POIGNANT MOMENT OF THE WEEK &LR; :
</P>
<P>
   Orrin Hatch, wishing to announce his withdrawal from the
Republican race, calls a press conference in Washington. The city
is hit by a fresh snowstorm and nobody comes. &QL; 
 &UR; ___________________ &LR;  &QC; 
