<HEADLINE>
PLUSH TOYS WITH A TWIST
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Purr-Fection by MJC is marketing Bendum-Buddies, a new line of
poseable plush toys manufactured with a flexible skeletonlike
mechanism that allows for fully articulated legs, arms, tails and
ears.
</P>
<P>
   The first 10 designs will be released in March: a Dalmatian dog
named Astro, a black bear named Kodiak, a tabby cat called
Crackers, a monkey who answers to Twig, a raccoon named Murphy, a
frog named Mason, a rabbit called Lily, and bears named Jake,
Maxine and Claude.
</P>
<P>
   The toys _ ranging in size from 12.5 to 18 inches tall _ each
retail for $15 to $25 at gift, toy, stationery, department,
hospital, florist and specialty stores. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
