<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FLOWERS-HOT-TIP-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE FLOWERS THAT BLOOM IN THE SPRING, TRA LA!
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: This story also moved to the ``e'' entertainment wire) 
 
 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Ever look a tagetes patula in the eye? Sure you have ... That's
a Tiger Eye French marigold, the little orange beauty that chases
aphids away from your roses.
</P>
<P>
   That's only one of the annuals _ flowering plants that last just
for a season _ you'll meet in ``Taylor's Guides Annuals'' (Hougton
Mifflin Co.; $23), edited by Barbara Ellis. The 442-page,
soft-cover compendium has probably every flower you've ever heard
of pictured or described between its covers, along with how-to
advice on growing and an interesting section on how to thwart
leafhoppers, beetles and other critters that like to eat annuals.
</P>
<P>
   There's a photo of every flower, so you know what to ask for at
the local nursery or what to look for on the seed rack. It's
available at bookstores or can be ordered by calling (800)
225-3362.
</P>
</TEXT>
