A1944 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r l BC-SACAGAWEA-COIN-HOT-TI     01-31 0205
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SACAGAWEA-COIN-HOT-TIP-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A STITCH IN TIME SAVES ... A DOLLAR
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: This story also moved to the ``e'' entertainment wire) 
 
 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   When the new Sacagawea dollar is issued by the U.S. Mint later
this year, you can spend it or you can save it. Or, if you're a
needleworker, you can reproduce it in floss.
</P>
<P>
   Posy Lough's The Posy Collection, which provides counted
cross-stitch graphs of historical sites and scenes, has released a
new cross-stitch kit depicting the female Shoshone scout who in
1804-05 helped explorers Lewis and Clark find the source of the
Mississippi River and open the Oregon Territory to exploration.
</P>
<P>
   The design, 4 1/4 inches by 5 inches on 14-count fabric, depicts
the young woman with her baby on her back. It also includes the
inscriptions ``Liberty,'' ``In God We Trust,'' and the year of
issue, 2000.
</P>
<P>
   The Sacagawea golden dollar coin counted cross-stitch kits are
available for $16 (including shipping and handling) from the Lewis
and Clark Center, 701 Riverside Drive, St. Charles, Mo. 63301;
(636) 947-3199; fax (636) 916-0240, or on the Web at
www.lewisclarkcenter.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
