Arizona predicts he will win Tuesday's New Hampshire primary and
spends the final 24 hours of campaigning in a whirlwind of events
from one end of the snowy state to another. By contrast, Texas Gov.
George W. Bush cancels a walk in downtown Exeter, to avoid
pro-marijuana protesters, and went sledding. By CLAY ROBISON and
R.G. RATCLIFFE.
