<HEADLINE>
BOMBS BURSTING IN AIR
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Mademoiselle magazine, breathless and buoyant, says that men are
turned on by images of women and balloons.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Cheryl Frazier &LR; , producer of a series of ``Bare Balloon Babe''
videos, says ``Some guys are Inflators _ they like to watch women
blowing up balloons _ while Poppers have more particular tastes:
Some like balloons popped by hand; others prefer high heels.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I know she's going to pop it,'' said one fan of the genre,
``but not when or how. It's thrilling.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Boy George  &LR; has made a series of TV ads for an Irish
insurance company.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Randall Koll &LR; , just back from New Orleans, reports that mega
successful novelist  &UR; Anne Rice  &LR; has opened a store that sells
``vampire-inspired novelties'' and ``wigs, shoes and jewelry that
Anne herself has worn _ all signed.'' Koll says that tags on the
wigs read ``worn by Novelist Anne Rice.''
</P>
<P>
   The store's  &UR; Esther Beeson &LR;  told us that the clothes include
items ``she wore on her book tours,'' for example, three wedding
dresses priced between $800 and $1,500.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Catherine Zeta-Jones &LR; , engaged to  &UR; Michael Douglas &LR;  and
pregnant by him, is apparently enthusiastic about his politics,
too. Douglas is a major supporter of Ploughshares, the San
Francisco Foundation that works for disarmament. The Times of
London says that Zeta-Jones has promised to join her fiance,
Archbishop  &UR; Desmond Tutu &LR;  and former President  &UR; Jimmy Carter &LR;  at a
disarmament conference in Atlanta later this month.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPARE PARTS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ The Barbie PC, released by Mattel last fall, contains about
half the educational software packed into the company's similar
computer for boys, the Hot Wheels PC. A Mattel spokeswoman told the
New York Times that programs such as Barbie Fashion Designer and
Detective Barbie used so much space that there wasn't room enough
for more educational software.
</P>
<P>
   _ Researchers at University of California at Irvine have
determined that right nostrils are able more than left to perceive
smells as more pleasant, but left nostrils are better at
identifying scents. The probable reason, says  &UR; Larry Cahill &LR;  in a
study published in New Scientist, is that one side of the brain
controls emotional processing, the other is logical and
calculating.
</P>
<P>
   _ New wrist devices are serving as cell phones, pagers, e-mail
readers, cameras, music players, TV sets, voice recorders, games,
compasses, weather stations and more. ``Timex is interest in the
real estate of the wrist,'' the watch company's  &UR; Susie &LR; 
 &UR; Watson &LR;  said. It's location, location, location. The wrist is the
most exciting and accessible place on the body.''
</P>
<P>
   _ But what about toes? ``The biggest unspoken fear men have when
it comes to footwear can be summed up in a word,'' says P.O.V.
magazine, in a story forwarded by  &UR; Ken Maley &LR; . ``Sandals. Brash in
the boardroom and brazen with women, men time and again find
themselves intimidated by the thought of actually buying a dress
sandal and using it as a weapon in the fashion arsenal. Fight on,
brothers.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LOVE LETTERS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ For a romantic dinner, says Bon Appetit, start with artichoke
petals, have pumpkin pie for dessert and use tall candles, because
``low votive candles make you look like Dracula.''
</P>
<P>
   _ The donkey population of Italy is dropping, so Milan ass
breeder  &UR; Eugenio Milonis &LR; , who presides over the Web site
www.asinomania.cjb.net, is using the Internet to find eligible sex
partners for his donkeys.
</P>
<P>
   ``If your donkey is lonely,'' says the banner on the site,
quoted in the Australian newspaper, ``send him to us.''
</P>
<P>
   ``When taken care of,'' says the site, ``the donkey is quick,
docile and hard-working. If not, it can become lazy, narrow-minded
and hard-headed. It will always take after its owner.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Putting on lipstick next to Milla Jovovich works for me. It
was like standing on a fashion set of all your favorite models.
There were two levels of women: those that were seven feet tall and
the rest of us. But I tell you, the taller lovelies have immense
feet. It made me feel much better about my height.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Liz Phair in Rolling Stone, about mingling with the
beautiful people at the recent VH1/ Vogue Fashion Awards.
</P>
</TEXT>
