Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ALLIED _ Allied Holdings is North America's leading car-hauler,
delivering more than 12 million new vehicles a year to dealerships
under contract to auto-makers. The problem with rising demand for
SUVs and trucks is that fewer of the bulky vehicles fit on a
trailer, cutting Allied's average load about 20 percent over the
last few years. That helped push the company's earnings into the
ditch for much of 1999 while Allied tried to adjust its pricing
structure, as well as recover from a mid-1998 strike at its biggest
customer, General Motors. fact box. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
