<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-31 18:25 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2162 &Cx1f; taf-z
s t BC-TRAVEL-BARGAINS-$ADV0     01-31 0498
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-BARGAINS-$ADV06-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TRAVELING THE NET 
</HEADLINE>
  (For release Sun., Feb. 6) 
(jt) 
 By JANET PIORKO    
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   SPRING ON THE RAILS _ Fares for the Euro-star train between
London and Paris or London and Brussels have been reduced for
travel between Feb. 15 and April 15. The one-way Spring Special
fare in second class (called standard class in Britain) during this
period is $89 instead of the leisure fare of $119 for either route;
the first-class fare is $149 instead of $199. The fares cannot be
booked until Feb. 15; they are nonrefundable and may not be
exchanged. Travel between London and Paris takes three hours;
London and Brussels, 2 hours and 36 minutes. For reservations,
contact Rail Europe, which distributes Euro-star tickets in the
United States, at (800) 387-6782 or at www.raileurope.com on the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
   FLYING TO AUSTRIA _ Austrian Airlines has a fare of $368 round
trip for midweek (Monday through Thursday) travel from New York to
Vienna for those who purchase tickets by March 15 and complete
their trips by April 6. Departure tax and airport fees of about $58
are additional. An optional three-night hotel package, including
lodging and Continental breakfast at a Vienna hotel, costs $105 a
person more through March, $135 from April 1 to 6. Reservations:
(800) 843-0002.
</P>
<P>
   SKIING IN CANADA _ A company called Skican has ski packages in
eastern and western Canada. A four-day, three-night package at Mont
Tremblant in the Laurentians starts at $435 a person, double
occupancy, including air fare from New York, through Feb. 12, or
$480 from Feb. 13 through March 18. The package includes three
nights' hotel, four days' car rental and three days' lift tickets.
Longer packages are also available, with a six-day, five-night
package starting at $650 from Sunday through March 18.
Accommodations are at Chateau Mont Tremblant.
</P>
<P>
   In the West, a seven-night package at Whistler starts at $925 a
person, double occupancy, at Whistler Creek Lodge from Feb. 9 to
Feb. 22 and $960 from Feb. 23 to March 21, including air fare from
New York and six days' lift tickets. There may be surcharges for
weekend travel. Many other options and destinations are available.
For more information, contact Skican: (800) 363-3009 or
www.skican.com.
</P>
<P>
   STOPOVER IN JORDAN _ Travelers who are flying Royal Jordanian
Airline from New York or Chicago to the Middle East (where the
carrier serves some 20 destinations) or the Far East can purchase a
two-night Jordan Stopover, starting at $94 a person, double
occupancy, that includes first-class hotel accommodations with
breakfast, a day's guided sightseeing tour with lunch, airport
transfers and taxes. The tour covers the capital of Amman as well
as biblical Madaba and Mount Nebo. Other sightseeing can be
substituted at extra cost, and tours can be purchased for the
second day. For information, contact Royal Jordanian's tour desk at
(212) 949-0070, extension 240.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
