   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Tuesday, Feb. 1. If you
have any questions, please call The Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
N-RELOCATE (Undated) - Some Navajos lost their homes to loan
sharks, some to tax liens. Others could not keep up with monthly
payments for water and electricity. But some, especially the young,
educated and culturally mobile, are flourishing away from the land
of their ancestors. By JERRY KAMMER. Story will move in the `A`
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
1918FLU (Phoenix) - Phoenix thought it could escape the devastation
of the 1918 flu pandemic, believing its balmy climate and habit of
sleeping in the fresh air would protect it from the worst of the
disease. Instead, the city was one of the few urban areas to suffer
two waves of influenza, which devastated its population. By BARBARA
YOST. Story moved in the `A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
TV-GOODY (Phoenix) - Two of Us, a VH1 movie about a fictional
meeting between John Lennon and Paul McCartney, might just as well
have been called ``Two Ex-Beatles Sittin' Around Talkin' '' because
by and large that's what it's about _ rock's greatest songwriters
hashing out (over a bit of hash or more likely, knowing McCartney's
tastes, marijuana) their differences. By BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story
will move in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
PIMENTEL-COLUMN (Phoenix) - Arizona Sen. John McCain has answered
the abortion question several times. We know he doesn't favor
abortion except in cases of rape or incest. From a public policy
standpoint, I have no difficulty discerning where he stands. McCain
was right both times when he said it would be his daughter's
decision and again when he said it would be the family's. It is her
decision, but it is not a decision she must make alone. Let's be
less enamored of ``gotcha'' journalism and more concerned with the
real question. I don't care what McCain would do with his own
daughter. I care what he would do with mine and yours. That's why
they call it public policy. &QL; 
By O. RICARDO PIMENTEL. Column will move in the ``K'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) - It was clear to me as long as I was
looking at it through the ninth floor windows of `The Arizona
Republic's` newsroom. A couple of Phoenix cops stopped a guy for
not having a headlamp on his bicycle and wound up shooting him
three times in the chest. Are you kiddin' me? If only I hadn't
gotten the idiotic notion to take the elevator to the ground floor,
get in my car and drive to 22nd Avenue and Monroe, where the
incident happened. By EJ MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and
``K'' categories. &QL;
