<HEADLINE>
AOL, AMERICAN TO OFFER LOYALTY AIR-TRAVEL PLAN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MATTHEW BRELIS  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   America Online Inc. and American Airlines will combine their
rewards program to create the largest on-line customer loyalty
program in the world.
</P>
<P>
   The three-year agreement between the nation's largest on-line
service provider and the second-largest airline will create AOL
AAdvantage and allow members to redeem points earned for air
travel, AOL membership fees and consumer products.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are essentially creating a whole new currency for the
on-line generation,'' said Don Carty, chairman and chief executive
of American Airlines. ``By teaming the first and largest
frequent-flier program with the world leader in interactive
services, we're establishing a powerful new brand that we think
will change the face of e-commerce.''
</P>
<P>
   Under the contract, first discussed last summer, the airline AOL
AAdvantage will be operated by a joint management team from
American Airlines and AOL's digital marketing services division.
</P>
<P>
   American's frequent-flier program, AAdvantage, has about 38
million members. America Online and its subsidiaries have some 22
million members.
</P>
<P>
   Glenn Engel, an airline analyst with Goldman Sachs &AMP; Co., said
the program will benefit American.
</P>
<P>
   ``Selling frequent-flier miles is a very profitable exercise for
the airlines. If you can increase the usage of the program, not
only is that good because it is profitable traffic to carry, it
also increases loyalty, which is what frequent-flier programs
started for.''
</P>
<P>
   By adding consumer products including books, CDs, and
appliances, the program also will take some pressure off American
to redeem the miles, Engel said.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Gunn, American's executive vice president for marketing and
planning, said America Online has bought a pool of miles from
American for promotional offerings and both companies will be
involved in selling miles to other companies, such as retailers,
that want to be involved in the reward program. The revenue from
sold miles and advertising on the site will be shared.
</P>
<P>
   Officials hope the program will be up and running by May.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
