<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES EDITOR'S NOTE FOR MONDAY, JAN. 31
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: This editor's note will appear in The New York Times on
Monday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-MARTHAS-VINEYARD-$ADV30-NYT (moved on Friday, Jan. 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Jan. 28,
described the many residents of Martha's Vineyard who repair for
the winter to other islands, in warmer climates. It mentioned Ed
Logue of West Tisbury, on the Vineyard, who was planning a month on
St. John, in the Virgin Islands.
</P>
<P>
   On Thursday, after the article had been edited, Logue, the
master planner of urban redevelopment in New Haven and Boston, died
at 78. His obituary appeared in The Times on Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
