<P>
   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   NH-INSURGENTS (Concord, N.H.) _ Republican John McCain and
Democrat Bill Bradley face dramatically different challenges in the
days ahead as they wrap up their campaigns in New Hampshire's
first-in-the-nation primary. McCain is hoping a strong New
Hampshire showing will enable him to make inroads against Texas
Gov. George Bush in battleground states that lie ahead. Bradley,
bracing for a setback at the hands of Vice President Al Gore, looks
to later primaries to rescue his faltering campaign. By STEWART M.
POWELL. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   NH-PRIMARY (Manchester, N.H.) _ Republican Sen. John McCain of
Arizona predicts he will win Tuesday's New Hampshire primary and
spends the final 24 hours of campaigning in a whirlwind of events
from one end of the snowy state to another. By contrast, Texas Gov.
George W. Bush cancels a walk in downtown Exeter, to avoid
pro-marijuana protesters, and went sledding. By CLAY ROBISON and
R.G. RATCLIFFE.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GOP-MARRIAGE (Washington) _ Rep. Bill Archer, R-Texas,
introduces the House Republicans' plan to ease the income tax
``marriage penalty'' paid by millions of two-income couples. By
JOHN HENRY.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   IMMIGRANT-KIDS (Harlingen, Texas) _ While the battle continues
over whether 6-year-old Elian Gonzalez should go back or stay, a
judge in a Rio Grande valley courtroom must decide what to do with
some children from Honduras whose parents cannot be located. By
JAMES PINKERTON.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
