<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer will be filing several stories
relating to the crash of Alaska Air Flight 261. If you have
questions, please call Mary Downes at the Post-Intelligencer
national desk at 206-448-8158.
</P>
<P>
   Among the stories expected:
</P>
<P>
   ALASKA-CRASH (Seattle) _ Main wrapup of the crash of Alaska Air
Flight 261 off Los Angeles. The jet was due to arrive in Seattle
Monday night after a stop in San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   By Paul Nyhan. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   ALASKA-CRASH-MAINTENANCE (Seattle) _ A criminal investigation
has been under way for months into maintenance practices of Alaska
Air in the San Francisco Bay area.
</P>
<P>
   By Scott Sunde. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   ALASKA-CRASH-PASSENGERS (Seattle) _ What we know about the
passengers and the crew, which was based in Seattle.)
</P>
<P>
   By Vanessa Ho. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   Other stories will move as they develop.
