<HEADLINE>
LOW BLOW FOR BAUER AND EXPECTATIONS
</HEADLINE>
  (nk) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANCHESTER, N.H. _ Lowering pundits' expectations is not a
problem for Gary Bauer.
</P>
<P>
   In a poll on the Republican presidential race released Tuesday
by CNN, USA Today and the Gallup Organization, Bauer was favored by
an unusually small percentage of the respondents: zero.
</P>
<P>
   Zero? Other polls out Tuesday, by the likes of The Associated
Press, the American Research Group and the University of New
Hampshire, put his support at 1 percent. When looked at from the
perspective of a forlorn zero, that sounded like quite a lot.
</P>
<P>
   Zero, of course, did not mean zero, but something akin to
``negligible.''
</P>
<P>
   William Schneider, CNN's senior political analyst, said that in
numerical terms it meant that of the 1,000 people interviewed for
the poll, fewer than one-half of 1 percent said they would vote for
Bauer on Tuesday. That works out to fewer than 5 people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
